data.description: Total package asking $300,000 for 8.6 acre horse farm, includes Home, concrete spa&pool, well & septic on 1 acre, another 1 acre with 6 stall Barn/Garage with well & septic, plus adjoining 6.6 acre pasture total package.  Fenced & crossed fenced, many improvements & upgrades to keep up with maintenance & modern styles.  Neighborhood Description: Tevalo Hills was developed in 1976.
data.whatILove: I love this home best because I lived on this land since 1976. We have watched this area grow & many people have prospered while living here. We built a cozy home, that turned into the best place to raise a family & small horse farm.  Many memories here with our family & our 4 legged friends.  This property is near several elementary schools within walking distance, or short drive, nearby are middle & senior high schools. Close to grocery stores, shopping, employment, churches, restaurant and recreational parks with fishing & swimming. Tevalo Hills sub-division developed in 1976. It's turned into a quite Community where homes are on 1+ Acre lots. Many original owners still live here. Ours is a quite street with newer homes built across the street. 2808 & 2810 Is where we raised our children, grand-children, and rode horses.  No restrictions or fees to live in neighborhood. Next door @2806 that is a family member owned property that is not part of this sale! Would consider selling for potential rental property if interested.
